Sexual dimorphism. None was found. Bony fin hooks, a common dimorphic feature of mature characid males (
Malabarba & Weitzman, 2003
) were not found in any of the specimens examined, including 15 c&s male specimens ( INPA 39505, 1 ex.; NUP 9543, 10 ex.; NUP 9545, 3 ex.; NUP 9546, 1 ex.) and several dissected males presenting mature testes (see “Ecological notes”, below).
